    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-10-23T14:15:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-10-19T19:14:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                <head>No. 410.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Curry</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>. [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1886-10-23T14:15:00-05:00" notBefore="1886-10-20T00:00:00-00:14">undated</date>]. (Received
                            October 23, 1886.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Curry asks to be informed whether Mr. Bayard’s telegram (of 22d) means
                        that he will accept the three propositions offered by the Government of
                        Spain if they are made to include the case of cargoes from foreign countries
                        arriving at the ports of Cuba and Porto Rico in vessels of the United
                        States.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
